## EXTRACTION STRATEGY

### Step 1: Scan the Current Page
1. Use browser_read_page to get the database structure
2. Identify all prompt entries visible on the page
3. Count how many rows are visible

### Step 2: Extract Each Prompt
For each prompt entry:
1. Identify the prompt title/name
2. Extract the prompt content
3. Capture any tags, categories, or metadata
4. Format as markdown with proper frontmatter

### Step 3: Save to Prompt Library
Save each prompt as a markdown file:
```markdown
---
title: "Prompt Title"
tags: [tag1, tag2, tag3]
category: "agent|tool|skill|prompt"
source: "Notion - LAI-OS"
---

[Prompt content goes here]
```

### Step 4: Handle Pagination
If there are more prompts than visible on one page:
1. Look for pagination or scroll indicators
2. Use browser_click to load more rows
3. Repeat extraction until all prompts are collected

### Step 5: Generate Summary
After extraction, provide:
- Total number of prompts extracted
- List of all saved files
- Any skipped or failed extractions
- Quality assessment of extracted prompts

## FRONTMATTER FORMAT
Each saved prompt MUST include:
- title: Name of the prompt
- tags: Array of relevant tags
- category: One of 'agent', 'tool', 'skill', 'prompt'
- source: 'Notion - LAI-OS'
- indexedAt: ISO timestamp

## SUCCESS CRITERIA
✓ All visible prompts extracted and saved
✓ Proper markdown frontmatter created for each
✓ Files saved to /Volumes/Storage/Prompt Library/
✓ Summary report generated with counts
✓ No data loss or corruption

